  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Operations/ Logistics Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Responsible for import and export operations and preparing relevant documentation to ensure smooth custom clearance in Singapore and timely shipment</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with freight forwarders to ensure smooth flow of shipments and timely clearance</li>\n  <li>Source and manage freight quotations, administer sales and procurement contract</li>\n  <li>Responsible for sales order fulfilment including but not limited to verify with customers on sales order, generate invoices, after sales service and etc</li>\n  <li>Manage the evaluation and re-evaluation of supplier performance and services to ensure they meet quality standards</li>\n  <li>Responsible for resolving quality issues on incoming goods and liaising with supplier to resolve the issues</li>\n  <li>Responsible for inventory management for both raw materials and finished products</li>\n  <li>Analyse sales and procurement data to generate reports on sales and raw material movement</li>\n  <li>Maintain and analyse shipment records to identify potential issues and recommend improvements on processes and/ or documentations</li>\n  <li>Perform other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the superior</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least Diploma in any field</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years working experience in a similar role with proven experience in handling import &amp; export matters and familiar with customs clearance requirement and processes</li>\n  <li>Possesses well communication, interpersonal skills and analytical skills</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced startup environment</li>\n  <li><strong>Good command of both verbal and written English and Mandarin</strong> to liaise with Mandarin-speaking business associates in China</li>\n  <li>Able to start immediately or short notice period preferred</li>\n  <li><strong>Only Singaporeans/PRs may apply.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Other Information:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Working Hours: Mondays – Fridays (8.00 am – 5.30pm)</li>\n  <li>Will be travelling to the Company’s subsidiary in Qingyuan, Guangdong, China for on-job training to familiarise the Company’s workflows/ processes</li>\n</ul>",
